The paper discusses deep reinforcement learning algorithms and their ability to transfer learning from one task to another. This topic falls under the category of machine learning, specifically reinforcement learning, which is covered in cs.LG. The paper also discusses regularization techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper evaluates the algorithms on simulated robots, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and systems and control (cs.SY).
